<br>
Also, people in general want what they can't have. We love the chase. I didn't even realise I did this until someone pointed it out to me. I personally know plenty of men who do this : /<br>
<br>
I don't know your situation Phyxious, but maybe things just didn't click for her. A guy can do everything 'right', but if the chemistry isn't there it won't work.. Or maybe she's not in a stage in her life where she wants that. I honestly think it's a confusing time for women. We don't know what we're supposed to want out of life anymore. At the end of the day I have to agree with Didi. Men and women alike don't always know what they want. I say/think I want one thing, then act in a different way and have to try to rationalise why I did it... back to the introspection again, fun.<br>
<br>
